column2: Question
If the election for governor were being held today, and the candidates were Republican Brian Kemp, Democrat Stacey Abrams, Libertarian Shane Hazel and Independent Al Bartel, for whom would you vote?
If the election for U.S. Senate were being held today, and the candidates were Republican Herschel Walker, Democrat Raphael Warnock and Libertarian Chase Oliver, for whom would you vote?
If the election for Lt. Governor were being held today, and the candidates were Republican Burt Jones, Democrat Charlie Bailey and Libertarian Ryan Graham, for whom would you vote?
If the election for Secretary of State were being held today, and the candidates were Republican Brad Raffensperger, Democrat Bee Nguyen and Libertarian Ted Metz, for whom would you vote?
If the election for Secretary of State were being held today, and the candidates were Republican Chris Carr, Democrat Jennifer Jordan  and Libertarian Martin Cowen, for whom would you vote?
All in all, do you think things in the nation are generally headed in the right direction, or do you think things are off on the wrong track?
In reference to Georgia specifically, do you think things in the state are generally headed in the right direction, or do you think things are off on the wrong track?
If the election were today, would you want to see the Republican Party or the Democratic Party win control of the U.S. Congress?
Do you approve or disapprove of the way Joe Biden is handling his job as president?
Do you approve or disapprove of the way Brian Kemp is handling his job as governor?
Do you approve or disapprove of the way Raphael Warnock is handling his job as U.S. Senator?
Does the Supreme Court’s decision overturning Roe versus Wade make you more motivated to vote in the 2022 midterm elections, less motivated, or will it make no difference?
Are you more likely to vote for a candidate who wants to protect access to abortion, wants to limit access to abortion, or does a candidate's position on abortion not make a difference in your vote?

Which one of these issues is the most important issue facing the country: threats to democracy, cost of living, jobs and the economy, immigration and border security, climate change, guns, abortion, crime, Covid-19?
What is the second most important issue facing the country?
How much of an impact have rising prices had on your day-to-day life?

column3: Noticeable, but not significantly negative impact

column2: Do you think the United States is doing enough to address climate change, doing too much, or do you think more needs to be done to address climate change?
How confident are you that the November election will be conducted fairly and accurately?

As you may know, President Biden has announced a plan to cancel some federal student loan debt for Americans earning less than $125,000 a year. Borrowers who are eligible would be forgiven $10,000 in federal student loan debt and those whoreceived Pell Grants would be forgiven up to $20,000. Do you approve or disapprove of President Biden's plan?

Do you support or oppose the recently passed $369 billion Inflation Reduction Act, which includes cuts to greenhouse gas emissions, gives government the ability to negotiate drug prices, and requires a minimum 15 percent tax on large corporations?

Thinking about the Fulton County grand jury investigation into actions by former President Donald Trump and his allies to change the outcome of the 2020 presidential election in Georgia, how much confidence do you have that the grand jury will conduct a fair and impartial investigation?
